{
  "texts": [
    "Amirmasoud Ahmadi et al. [17] presented a new algorithm for seizure classification using the wavelet packet transform (WPT) to identify the essential characteristics of the signal better.",
    "They used a public database from the Epilepsy Centre at Bonn University, which contained EEG signals from five healthy and five patients with epilepsy.",
    "This dataset was divided into 17 subsegments that, in turn, were organized into WP trees.",
    "From these coefficients, they used statistical characteristics such as standard deviation (STD) and root mean square (RMS).",
    "Then, they used the Support vector machine (SVM) classifier for binary classification in seven cases."
  ]
}